    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How does the font identifier work?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The font identifier uses a guided questionnaire that asks about visual characteristics of the font you're trying to identify — such as whether it has serifs, its stroke weight, x-height, letter shapes, and overall style. Based on your answers, it narrows down matches from a curated database of 50+ popular Google Fonts and system fonts, showing live previews of each match."
