        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I compare fonts side by side?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes. The font comparison mode lets you type custom text and see it rendered in up to three fonts simultaneously. This makes it easy to spot subtle differences between similar typefaces and pick the one that best matches the font you're trying to identify."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What fonts are included in the database?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The database includes over 50 popular fonts from Google Fonts and common system fonts. It covers a wide range of categories including serif, sans-serif, monospace, display, and handwriting fonts. Each font is tagged with visual characteristics like stroke contrast, x-height, letter roundness, and more."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is this tool free to use?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, the font identifier is completely free. It runs entirely in your browser with no uploads, no sign-ups, and no limits. Font previews are loaded from Google Fonts, which is also free for both personal and commercial use."
        }
